ge_size = \n| caption = \n| motto = \n| mottoeng = \"I am the city of learning and Ali is its gate\"\n| established = {{Start date and age| 1925|10|25}}\n| founder = \n| type = Minority\n| students = \n| city = [[Lucknow]]\n| state = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| country = [[India]]\n| campus = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| colors = \n| website = {{URL|http://shiacollege.org/}} & {{URL|https://shiapgcollege.ac.in/}}\n| logo = \n| affiliation = [[Lucknow University]]\n}}\n'''Shia College''' is a [[college]] located in old [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]. It is affiliated with the [[University of Lucknow]] and one of the institutes of higher education in India.<ref name='Dir'> The direcotories & listings containing 'Shia College' or 'Shia Degree College',\n* {{Cite book|last=Padmavathi|first=Padala|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Ksc1S2SEzr8C&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+college%22|title=The Directory of Indian Higher Educational Institutions - Shia College|date=1970|publisher=copies can be had from Panchayat Publications|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Padmavathi|first=Padala|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Ksc1S2SEzr8C&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+degree+college%22|title=The Directory of Indian Higher Educational Institutions - Shia Degree College|date=1970|publisher=copies can be had from Panchayat Publications|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=sEIWAQAAIAAJ&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+college%22|title=Directory of Educational Institutions|publisher=R. P. Bookwala.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=JwZRAAAAYAAJ&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+college%22|title=The World of Learning|date=1970|publisher=Allen & Unwin|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=oKgZAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQg1MAI|title=Commonwealth Universities Yearbook|date=1963|publisher=Association of Commonwealth Universities.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=HV8dAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQhaMAc|title=The Indian Year Book|date=1942|publisher=Bennett, Coleman & Company|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Padmavathi|first=Padala|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Ksc1S2SEzr8C&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQhhMAg|title=The Directory of Indian Higher Educational Institutions|date=1970|publisher=copies can be had from] Panchayat Publications|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Rao|first=T. V. Rama|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=2b9NOnb8WigC&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQhnMAk|title=India at a Glance: A Comprehensive Reference Book on India|last2=Binani|first2=G. D.|date=1954|publisher=Orient Longmans|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=6f1OnwAIIzEC&pg=RA1-PA364&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEgNn2uv7oAhXC2qQKHVw2Djs4FBDoAQgnMAA|title=Government Gazette: The United Provinces of Agra and Oudh|date=1922|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Education|first=India Ministry of|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=qLfjAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEgNn2uv7oAhXC2qQKHVw2Djs4FBDoAQhiMAg|title=Directory of Institutions for Higher Education|date=1981|publisher=Ministry of Education and Social Welfare.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Reed|first=Sir Stanley|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=NG0iAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEgNn2uv7oAhXC2qQKHVw2Djs4FBDoAQhqMAk|title=The Times of India Directory and Year Book Including Who's who|date=1962|publisher=Bennett, Coleman.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=sEIWAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi6g8zMvP7oAhXSy6QKHSbYCA04HhDoAQhHMAU|title=Directory of Educational Institutions|publisher=R. P. Bookwala.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Commission|first=India University Grants|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=fWXKUtTMqTcC&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi6g8zMvP7oAhXSy6QKHSbYCA04HhDoAQhOMAY|title=Bulletin of Higher Education|date=1975|publisher=University Grants Commission.|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Pradesh (India)|first=Uttar|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=z-9FAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiGkoGRwP7oAhXDzaQKHRTZBpg4KBDoAQguMAE|title=Uttar Pradesh district gazetteers|date=1959|publisher=Govt. of Uttar Pradesh|language=en}}\n</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Hasnain|first=Nadeem|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=fjO6DQAAQBAJ&q=The+World+of+Shias#v=snippet&q=The%20World%20of%20Shias&f=false|title=The Other Lucknow|date=2016|publisher=Vani Prakashan|isbn=978-93-5229-420-6|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Overview ==\nShia college was established in 1919. Over a period of 100 years of its existence the college has contributed immensely to Indian society with its impressive alumni comprising academicians, politicians, bureaucrats and other distinguished citizens. Although The college was established just a year before the [[Lucknow University]] came into existence, it was initially affiliated to [[Allahabad University]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Allahabad|first=University of|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=xVY4AAAAMAAJ&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+college%22|title=Calendar|date=1922|publisher=University of Allahabad|language=en}}</ref> The College consists of two teaching campuses viz, Sitapur Road Campus and Victoria Street Campus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://shiacollege.org/page.php?d=1|title=Shia College, Lucknow - Introduction|website=shiacollege.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Brief history==\nThe idea of starting a Shia College was formulated in [[All India Shia Political Conference|AISC]]'s 1910 session,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=8NQ_AAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwibxuSowv7oAhXTwAIHHQFjCSM4RhDoAQg2MAI|title=Grassroots|date=2000|publisher=Pakistan Studies Centre, University of Sind|language=en}}</ref> the scheme was floated in March 1914 and the decision of starting a degree college at Lucknow was taken in 1915.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Khan|first=Abdul Rashid|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=DRFuAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwibxuSowv7oAhXTwAIHHQFjCSM4RhDoAQhLMAU|title=The All India Muslim Educational Conference: Its Contribution to the Cultural Development of Indian Muslims, 1886-1947|date=2001|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-579375-8|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=AxVDAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwibxuSowv7oAhXTwAIHHQFjCSM4RhDoAQhEMAQ|title=Pioneer Mail and Indian Weekly News|date=1920|language=en}}</ref> In 1917 [[List of Lieutenant-Governors of the United Provinces of Agra and Oudh|Governor]] [[James Meston, 1st Baron Meston|James Meston]] laid foundation stone for it,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Rieck|first=Andreas|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=2HdeCwAAQBAJ&q=%22shia+college%22#v=snippet&q=%22shia%20college%22&f=false|title=The Shias of Pakistan: An Assertive and Beleaguered Minority|date=2016-01-15|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-061348-8|language=en}}</ref> and it was completed between 1928-34.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Misra|first=A. K.|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=hruOAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwibxuSowv7oAhXTwAIHHQFjCSM4RhDoAQhTMAY|title=Administrative History of Modern India: Sir Malcolm Haley's Ideas, Policies, and Activities in the United Provinces of Agra and Oudh, 1928-34|date=1992|publisher=Print House (India)|isbn=978-81-85009-39-1|language=en}}</ref> Donations came from all members of [[Shia Islam in the Indian subcontinent|Shia community]], the major shares from [[Category:Nawabs of India|nawabs]], [[Taluqdar|taluqedars]] & [[Shia clergy|clergy]] like [[Nawab Fateh Ali Khan Kazilbash|Nawab Kazilbash]](Shia College was his brainchild<ref name='Memories'>{{Cite book|last=Graff|first=Violette|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=PUlwAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEgNn2uv7oAhXC2qQKHVw2Djs4FBDoAQhbMAc|title=Lucknow: Memories of a City|date=1999|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-564887-4|language=en}}</ref>), [[Hamid Ali Khan of Rampur|Nawab Rampur]], [[Mohammad Ali Mohammad Khan|Raja Mahmudabad]](he was initially opposed to idea of Shia College<ref name='Memories'/>), [[Najmul Hasan]], etc.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=GJNAAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwibxuSowv7oAhXTwAIHHQFjCSM4RhDoAQg9MAM|title=Men and Missions|date=1916|publisher=Laymen's Missionary Movement.|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=PWY0AQAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjd9PCtwf7oAhUG6qQKHWarAK84PBDoAQg0MAI|title=The Lutheran Companion|date=1917|publisher=Augustana Book Concern|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=5V9MAAAAYAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjd9PCtwf7oAhUG6qQKHWarAK84PBDoAQg7MAM|title=Young Lutheran's Companion|date=1917|publisher=Augustana Book Concern|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=DTHlAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiGkoGRwP7oAhXDzaQKHRTZBpg4KBDoAQhCMAQ|title=The Times of India Directory and Year Book Including Who's who|date=1950|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=vTBRAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQg8MAM|title=Cambridge South Asian Studies|date=1965|isbn=978-0-521-20432-3|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=WOqwAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQhTMAY|title=Economic and Political Weekly|date=1996|publisher=Sameeksha Trust|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Hasan, Amir, 1929-|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/21297189|title=Vanishing culture of Lucknow|date=1990|publisher=B.R. Pub. Corp|isbn=81-7018-573-4|location=Delhi|oclc=21297189}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=JvsKAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjloe-xrv7oAhUECewKHehACkQQ6AEIcjAJ|title=Islam and the Modern Age|date=1992|publisher=Islam and the Modern Age Society.|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Hasan|first=Amir|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=kytvAAAAMAAJ&q=shia+college+lucknow&dq=shia+college+lucknow&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwje24uumv7oAhUD-6QKHfvsApgQ6AEIejAK|title=Vanishing Culture of Lucknow|date=1990|publisher=B.R. Publishing Corporation|isbn=978-81-7018-573-4|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Salam|first=Ziya Us|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=f-u9DwAAQBAJ&q=%22shia+college%22#v=snippet&q=%22shia%20college%22&f=false|title=Madrasas in the Age of Islamophobia|last2=Parvaiz|first2=Mohammad Aslam|date=2020-01-07|publisher=SAGE Publishing India|isbn=978-93-5328-930-0|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Hasnain|first=Nadeem|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=OgtuAAAAMAAJ&dq=shia+college+lucknow&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22shia+college%22|title=Shias and Shia Islam in India: a study in society and culture|last2=Husain|first2=Sheikh Abrar|date=1988|publisher=Harnam Publications|language=en}}</ref> Shia College was established on 25 October 1917.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Butler|first=Sir Harcourt|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=O5yGCsM4h34C&pg=PA15&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi6g8zMvP7oAhXSy6QKHSbYCA04HhDoAQhWMAc|title=Speeches, 15th Feb., 1918, to 2nd Jan., 1921|date=1921|publisher=Superintendent,] Government Press|language=en}}</ref> But due to government restrictions Shia College initially started functioning as a school in the premises of [[Bada Imambara]] in 1919. In 1922 it became Intermediate College, teaching started with subjects in Humanities and Social Sciences while Natural Sciences was introduced in 1932. In 1947 the college was allowed to start degree classes in science, when the University of Lucknow decided  to permit the teaching of Science out side the premises of [[Canning College]]. Later on Bachelor in 1960, Bachelor of Laws in 1970, Bachelor of Commerce in 1972, B.Sc. Computer Science in 1989. The College attained Post-Graduate level in 1995 with M.A. in Urdu; later on M.A. in Sociology in 1996, M.Com. in Applied  Economics in 2005, M.Sc. in Zoology and M.Com.in Pure  Commerce in 2006, M.A. in Journalism & Mass Communication in 2007, M.Sc./M.A. in Statistics in 2008. Professional management course Bachelor of Business Administration in International Business was started in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://shiacollege.org/page.php?d=38|title=Shia College, Lucknow - History|website=shiacollege.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Notable principals & board members==\n===Principals===\n* [[Syed Sibte Hasan Naqvi]] (d. 1935), ex-principal\n* [[Syed Mohammad Waris Hasan Naqvi]] (d. 11 May 2008), ex-principal\n\n===Board members===\n* [[Syed Ali Zaheer]] (1896-1983), president of the College Management Committee\n* [[Syed Muzaffar Husain Rizvi]](1932 \u2013 Dec 1987), founding member of the governing board\n* [[Syed Ali Nasir Saeed Abaqati]], ex-board member\n\n==Notable alumni==\n* [[Rasheed Turabi]] (1908\u20131973), an Islamic scholar, religious leader, public speaker, poet and philosopher.\n* [[Arif Mohammad Khan]] (b. 18 November 1951), an Indian politician, currently the [[Governor of Kerala]], 3 times [[Member of parliament|MP]] of [[Lok sabha]] and erstwhile cabinet minister.\n* [[Syed Wajih Ahmad Naqvi]], Indian marine scientist and the former director of the [[National Institute of Oceanography, India|National Institute of Oceanography]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Cite book|last=Butler|first=Sir Harcourt|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=O5yGCsM4h34C&pg=PA15&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi6g8zMvP7oAhXSy6QKHSbYCA04HhDoAQhWMAc|title=Speeches, 15th Feb., 1918, to 2nd Jan., 1921|date=1921|publisher=Superintendent,] Government Press|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Marris|first=Sir William|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Wsg9AAAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjHos6ctv7oAhVGCuwKHcXyCt44ChDoAQhMMAU|title=The Speeches of Sir William Marris: As Governor of the United Provinces of Agra and Oudh : December 1922-January 1928|date=1928|publisher=Wesleyan Mission Press|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Ghosh|first=Abinaschandra|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=C1Q3AAAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjd9PCtwf7oAhUG6qQKHWarAK84PBDoAQgtMAE|title=The law of endowments (Hindu & Mahomedan): with introduction, history of the origin and development of the charitable and religious institutions in India, and the laws governing them : including the procedure, and all the imperial and local acts, model forms of deeds, pleadings and rules|date=1938|publisher=Eastern Law House|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Assembly|first=Uttar Pradesh (India) Legislature Legislative|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=l20lAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Shia+College%22&dq=%22Shia+College%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjz_ajewP7oAhXS